1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on the role of peer influence in churn in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) - The paper also examines the effect of group churn, which is a social phenomenon, and how it can be prevented. 
3. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) - The paper may also be relevant to the cybersecurity and privacy sub-category, as churn can be caused by security breaches or privacy concerns. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper uses survival models and generalized propensity score to analyze the data, which are techniques commonly used in multiagent systems. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also be relevant to the cryptography and security sub-category, as churn can be caused by security breaches or fraud.
